{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fe1724e9-a383-4468-af84-43289db0167f","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **xUnit** is unique — skip is a property on `[Fact]`/`[Theory]`, not a separate attribute.\n- **MSTest & NUnit** both use `[Ignore(\"reason\")]`, but they're different types from different namespaces.\n- **TUnit** uses `[Skip(\"reason\")]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5d8a79e1-8d49-4625-a4ac-fcdb74d8f968","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax for skipping tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":283,"requestId":"9819:3A3A20:1B04B6:23605F:69FFDC49"},"id":"def6af2b-a379-4b0d-bd92-30d5b9e15e24","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:16:01.062Z","parentId":"1400ed54-aa39-4c93-967a-16e700e922e6"}
